About

Customer is willing to buy an Omnia FT-250, on 1 condition: we need to be able to sort the different 'shades' of green eggs.

Happen

Investigate the possibility and costs to adapt the Blood/Brown detector to scan green eggs in the same way as we currently clasify brown eggs in a number of different levels
As with the current brown detection, it must be possible to grade the eggs according to their green colour. White eggs should have their own clasification too.

Consider

  Customer uses 99% green eggs and 1% white eggs. < in the same batch?>

Problems

  DOS environment causes restrictions in software capabilities, meaning the solution must work, but a rather quick and dirty solution is acceptable.

Expect

If possible, we expect a solution that can grade green eggs on colour, similar to the capabilities of the brown detection. We also expect a clear description with regard to the conditions under which this functionality can operate.

Info

Contact Ed van Steeg for consult
